    <!-- Info tooltips -->
    <string name="info_telescopic">Telescopic billing applies when monthly consumption is 250 units or less. Each slab is charged independently at its own rate — you pay the lower rate for the first units and progressively higher rates only for units in higher slabs.</string>
    <string name="info_non_telescopic">Non-telescopic billing applies when monthly consumption exceeds 250 units. A single flat rate is applied to ALL consumed units (not just the excess over 250). This means the bill can jump significantly at the 251-unit boundary.</string>
    <string name="info_electricity_duty">Electricity Duty is a state government levy calculated as a percentage of the energy charge. Currently 10%% of the total energy charge.</string>
    <string name="info_fuel_surcharge">Fuel Surcharge is an additional per-unit charge that KSEB levies to recover fuel cost variations. This rate changes periodically.</string>

